1
00:00:03,919 --> 00:00:07,791
[柯克] 舰长日志，星历5423.4
[Kirk] Captain's Log : Star date 5423.4.

2
00:00:07,860 --> 00:00:10,535
我们正在绕吉迪恩运行，它还不是
We are orbiting the planet Gideon, which is still not a member...

3
00:00:10,607 --> 00:00:12,527
星际联邦成员
of the United Federation of Planets.

4
00:00:12,594 --> 00:00:14,739
条约谈判一直很艰难
The treaty negotiations have been difficult...

5
00:00:14,814 --> 00:00:16,858
吉迪恩一直拒绝
because Gideon has consistently refused...

6
00:00:16,933 --> 00:00:20,671
联邦代表团踏入他们的国土
the presence of a delegation from the Federation on its soil...

7
00:00:20,742 --> 00:00:23,158
或飞船传感器的任何监视
or any surveillance by the ship's sensors.

8
00:00:23,226 --> 00:00:25,935
他们最终同意由一人组成的代表团
They have finally agreed to a delegation of one.

9
00:00:26,008 --> 00:00:29,509
他们坚持要求是企业号的舰长
They insisted it be the captain of the Enterprise.

10
00:00:29,584 --> 00:00:33,186
因此，我要立即传送下去
I am, therefore, beaming down at once.

11
00:00:33,260 --> 00:00:36,003
真可惜吉迪恩不允许集体访问，史波克先生
It's too bad Gideon isn't cleared for general visitation, Mr. Spock.

12
00:00:36,075 --> 00:00:37,858
根据提交给联邦的
According to the physio cultural reports...

13
00:00:37,930 --> 00:00:39,816
自然文化报告，它是天堂
submitted to the Federation, it's a paradise.

14
00:00:39,883 --> 00:00:42,356
我很想听听你的描述，舰长
I shall be interested in hearing your description, Captain.

15
00:00:42,434 --> 00:00:45,143
不会让你久等的
You won't have long to wait.

16
00:00:45,215 --> 00:00:47,225
- 乌乎拉上尉  - 是的，史波克先生
- Lieutenant Uhura. - Yes, Mr. Spock.

17
00:00:47,302 --> 00:00:49,255
我们得到吉迪恩的最终批准了吗？
Do we have final clearance from Gideon?

18
00:00:49,322 --> 00:00:52,631
是的，他们为我们提供了坐标
Yes. They have provided us with the coordinates for beam down.

19
00:00:52,700 --> 00:00:54,676
把坐标给我好吗？
May I have them, please?

20
00:00:54,753 --> 00:00:57,756
- 875  - 875
- 875. - 875.

21
00:00:57,833 --> 00:01:00,339
- 020  - 020
- 020. - 020.

22
00:01:00,416 --> 00:01:02,336
[乌乎拉] 079
[Uhura] 079.

23
00:01:02,403 --> 00:01:05,746
079
079.

24
00:01:05,814 --> 00:01:08,162
我们走吧，史波克先生
Let's go, Mr. Spock.

25
00:01:08,232 --> 00:01:10,151
传送
Energizing.

26
00:01:30,992 --> 00:01:33,491
史波克先生？
Mr. Spock?

27
00:01:36,334 --> 00:01:38,932
史波克先生，我还没有被传送下去
Mr. Spock. I have not yet transported down.

28
00:01:39,005 --> 00:01:43,103
你为什么在确认传送之前离开你的岗位？
Why did you leave your post before confirming transport?

29
00:01:43,174 --> 00:01:46,095
史波克先生？
Mr. Spock?

30
00:01:46,171 --> 00:01:48,548
史波克？
Spock?

31
00:02:15,982 --> 00:02:18,917
轮机部？斯科特先生？
Engineering. Mr. Scott?

32
00:02:18,985 --> 00:02:20,919
斯科提？
Scotty!

33
00:02:23,490 --> 00:02:26,118
乌乎拉上尉，马上报告
Lieutenant Uhura, report immediately.

34
00:02:27,761 --> 00:02:31,527
所有舰桥人员，立即回答
All bridge personnel, report immediately.

35
00:02:31,598 --> 00:02:35,159
柯克呼叫船员，船上有人吗？
Kirk to crew. Is anyone aboard?

36
00:02:39,339 --> 00:02:41,330
医务室？麦考伊医生？
Sick Bay. Dr. McCoy?

37
00:02:42,609 --> 00:02:45,806
老骨头，老骨头，回答我
Bones? Bones, answer me.

38
00:02:47,347 --> 00:02:49,281
老骨头…
Bones.

39
00:03:07,319 --> 00:03:09,617
我们仍在绕吉迪恩运行
We're still orbiting Gideon.

40
00:03:30,543 --> 00:03:33,569
[柯克] 宇宙，最后的边疆
[Kirk] Space, the final frontier.

41
00:03:39,585 --> 00:03:43,851
这些是星舰企业号的航程
These are the voyages of the star ship Enterprise.

42
00:03:43,923 --> 00:03:47,859
它的五年任务：探索未知的新世界
Its five-year mission: to explore strange new worlds,

43
00:03:47,927 --> 00:03:51,920
寻找新生命和新文明
to seek out new life and new civilizations,

44
00:03:51,997 --> 00:03:55,194
勇踏前人未至之境
to boldly go where no man has gone before.

45
00:04:28,185 --> 00:04:30,313
吉迪恩的伤口
The Mark of Gideon

46
00:04:49,636 --> 00:04:52,434
我一个人在企业号上
I'm alone on the Enterprise.

47
00:04:52,505 --> 00:04:56,999
我已经搜遍了船上的每个区域，都找不到船员的踪迹
I have searched the ship and still cannot find a trace of the crew...

48
00:04:57,077 --> 00:05:01,480
或船员如何消失的迹象
or an indication of how its disappearance was managed.

49
00:05:01,548 --> 00:05:04,346
一件事显而易见，我经历了一次失忆
The one thing that is obvious is that I suffered a memory lapse...

50
00:05:04,417 --> 00:05:07,215
在那段时间里，我的手臂受伤了
during which time I bruised my arm.

51
00:05:07,287 --> 00:05:09,619
这让我有些恼火
It is causing me some irritation.

52
00:05:09,689 --> 00:05:13,090
吉迪恩人正在联系我们，史波克先生
Gideon is contacting us, Mr. Spock.

53
00:05:14,661 --> 00:05:16,629
- 把它放在屏幕上  - 是的，长官
- Put it on the screen. - Aye, sir.

54
00:05:18,298 --> 00:05:22,564
柯克舰长，我是霍丁大使
Captain Kirk. This is Ambassador Hodin.

55
00:05:22,636 --> 00:05:25,104
议会正在等待您的到来
The council is still awaiting your arrival.

56
00:05:25,171 --> 00:05:28,231
我是史波克先生，霍丁大使
This is Mr. Spock, Ambassador Hodin.

57
00:05:28,308 --> 00:05:31,004
柯克舰长几分钟前就被传送下去了
Captain Kirk was transported down minutes ago.

58
00:05:31,077 --> 00:05:35,013
- 那不可能，- 我亲自传送的他
- That's impossible. - I transported him myself.

59
00:05:35,081 --> 00:05:38,209
他从未到过
He never arrived.

60
00:05:38,284 --> 00:05:40,775
他被直接传送到了你的议会厅
He was beamed directly to your council chambers.

61
00:05:40,854 --> 00:05:42,845
请验证您的坐标
Please verify your coordinates.

62
00:05:46,226 --> 00:05:48,421
875
875.

63
00:05:48,495 --> 00:05:50,588
020
020.

64
00:05:50,664 --> 00:05:54,031
- 079  - 坐标已确认
- 079. - Coordinates confirmed.

65
00:05:54,100 --> 00:05:56,534
我们给了你准确的坐标
We gave you the exact coordinates,

66
00:05:56,603 --> 00:06:00,505
这应该把柯克舰长带到这个房间里
which should have brought Captain Kirk directly to this very room.

67
00:06:00,573 --> 00:06:02,700
我没有质疑这一点，先生
I am not questioning that, sir.

68
00:06:02,776 --> 00:06:07,475
如果他不在这，史波克先生
If he is not here, that is your own responsibility, Mr. Spock,

69
00:06:07,547 --> 00:06:09,481
那是你自己和你的员工的责任
and that of your staff.

70
00:06:09,549 --> 00:06:14,384
我不否认这一点，我并不是要责怪你们的人员
I do not deny that, sir. I am not attempting to blame your personnel.

71
00:06:14,454 --> 00:06:16,388
很高兴听到它
We are glad to hear that.

72
00:06:16,456 --> 00:06:21,052
我们将把它记入这次不幸事件的记录中
We shall enter it into the records of this most unfortunate event.

73
00:06:21,127 --> 00:06:24,494
阁下，即使有像我们这样
Your Excellency, even with intricate machinery...

74
00:06:24,564 --> 00:06:26,498
微妙平衡的复杂机器
as delicately balanced as ours,

75
00:06:26,566 --> 00:06:29,330
也有处理错误的余地
there is still a margin for error which must be dealt with.

76
00:06:29,402 --> 00:06:31,370
有可能柯克舰长
It is possible that Captain Kirk...

77
00:06:31,438 --> 00:06:34,407
在吉迪恩的另一处物质化
materialized on some other part of Gideon.

78
00:06:34,474 --> 00:06:36,533
希望是在陆地上
Let us hope it was on dry land.

79
00:06:36,609 --> 00:06:40,670
阁下
Your Excellency.

80
00:06:40,747 --> 00:06:42,738
我可以切入正题吗？
May I cut right to the heart of the matter?

81
00:06:42,816 --> 00:06:47,685
请允许我传送下来进行搜索
I request permission to beam down.

82
00:06:47,754 --> 00:06:52,714
拒绝，你们联邦一定知道我们坚守的传统
Permission denied.Your Federation must be aware of our jealous tradition of isolation...

83
00:06:52,792 --> 00:06:55,590
避免一切污染性接触
from all contaminating contacts...

84
00:06:55,662 --> 00:06:59,621
与其他星系行星的暴力性质隔离开来
with a violent nature of planets of other star systems.

85
00:06:59,699 --> 00:07:03,931
阁下，敌对星系之间的战争
Your Excellency, the wars between opposing star systems...

86
00:07:04,003 --> 00:07:06,995
在我们的星系中不再盛行
no longer prevail in our galaxy.

87
00:07:07,073 --> 00:07:08,665
如果您能授予权限…
If you will grant permission

88
00:07:08,742 --> 00:07:11,210
我们将进行彻底的搜索
Of course, we shall institute a thorough search.

89
00:07:11,277 --> 00:07:16,112
与此同时，史波克先生，我建议您检查一下你的机器
In the meantime, I suggest that you look to your machinery.

90
00:07:16,182 --> 00:07:18,207
[舒一口气] 
[ Sighs ] 

91
00:07:18,284 --> 00:07:22,983
我们必须彻底承认外交的目的
We must acknowledge once and for all that the purpose of diplomacy...

92
00:07:23,056 --> 00:07:25,991
是延长危机
is to prolong a crisis.

93
00:07:26,059 --> 00:07:28,926
那我们还在等什么？我们又不是外交官
Well, what are we waiting for? We're not diplomats!

94
00:07:28,995 --> 00:07:31,759
我们是联邦的代表，医生
We are representatives of the Federation, Doctor.

95
00:07:31,831 --> 00:07:37,201
这并不意味着我们必须表现得像孩子一样，听外交官的愚蠢演讲
That doesn't mean we have to listen to some fool lecture by a diplomat!

96
00:07:37,270 --> 00:07:40,899
不幸的是，外交是我们目前唯一可用的方式
Unfortunately, diplomacy is the only channel available at the moment.

97
00:07:40,974 --> 00:07:44,705
星球屏蔽了我们的传感器，我们无法扫描它
The planet is shielded from our sensors. We cannot scan it.

98
00:07:44,778 --> 00:07:49,545
我们无法选择坐标，必须由吉迪恩人提供
We are unable to select coordinates. They must be provided by Gideon.

99
00:07:49,616 --> 00:07:52,244
我们就不应该同意规定
We should never have agreed to such restrictions.

100
00:07:52,318 --> 00:07:56,084
我们没有，契科夫先生，是联邦
We did not, Mr. Chekov. The Federation did.

101
00:07:56,156 --> 00:07:58,090
- 乌乎拉上尉  - 是的，史波克先生
- Lieutenant Uhura. - Yes, Mr. Spock.

102
00:07:58,158 --> 00:08:00,854
立即联系星际舰队，说明我们的问题
Contact Starfleet immediately. Explain our problem.

103
00:08:00,927 --> 00:08:03,418
请求允许使用我们可以使用的一切手段
Request permission to use every means at our disposal...

104
00:08:03,496 --> 00:08:05,157
来搜寻柯克舰长
to press the search for Captain Kirk.

105
00:08:05,231 --> 00:08:09,895
- 马上，长官  - 有其他可能吗？
- At once, sir. - Are there any other possibilities?

106
00:08:09,969 --> 00:08:12,130
有无数可能，契科夫先生
There are endless, Mr. Chekov.

107
00:08:12,205 --> 00:08:14,537
那我们从哪里开始，史波克先生？
Well, where do we start, Mr. Spock?

108
00:08:14,607 --> 00:08:18,168
使用传感器扫描360度
Institute a sensor scan 360 degrees,

109
00:08:18,244 --> 00:08:21,008
每次1度
one degree at a time.

110
00:08:21,080 --> 00:08:23,378
你是说你要为他扫描空间？
You mean you're gonna scan space for him?

111
00:08:23,449 --> 00:08:28,113
- 但这可能需要数年时间  - 那么越早开始越好
- But, sir, that could take years. - The sooner you begin, the better.

112
00:08:28,621 --> 00:08:30,918
是的，长官
Aye, sir.

113
00:08:37,063 --> 00:08:39,156
[开门] 
[Door Opens] 

114
00:08:58,751 --> 00:09:00,810
你是谁？
Who are you?

115
00:09:03,556 --> 00:09:08,357
奥多纳，是的，我的名字是奥多纳
Odona! Yes, my name is Odona.

116
00:09:09,729 --> 00:09:12,220
你为什么把我带来这里？
Why did you bring me here?

117
00:09:12,298 --> 00:09:14,528
你在我的船上做什么？
What are you doing on my ship?

118
00:09:16,836 --> 00:09:19,805
这整艘船是你的吗？
Is this entire ship yours?

119
00:09:19,873 --> 00:09:22,899
不是我的私人财产，但我是舰长
Not my personal property, but I'm the captain.

120
00:09:22,976 --> 00:09:25,809
你拥有这一切吗？
Oh, and you have it all to yourself?

121
00:09:25,879 --> 00:09:28,780
目前看来，是我们拥有一切
It seems, at the moment, we have it all to ourselves.

122
00:09:28,848 --> 00:09:30,247
噢！
Oh!

123
00:09:30,316 --> 00:09:33,547
你弄疼我了，舰长
You're hurting me, Captain

124
00:09:33,620 --> 00:09:38,148
柯克，抱歉，詹姆斯·柯克，而且不是我带你来的
Kirk. I'm sorry. James Kirk. And I didn't bring you here.

125
00:09:38,224 --> 00:09:41,990
- 如果不是你带我来的…  - 是的，谁带你来的？
- If you didn't bring me... - That's right. Who brought you here?

126
00:09:43,062 --> 00:09:44,996
我不知道
I don't know.

127
00:09:45,064 --> 00:09:47,430
你…
You

128
00:09:50,969 --> 00:09:52,768
你来之前发生了什么？
What happened before you came here?

129
00:09:54,107 --> 00:09:56,974
试着回忆，这很重要
Try to remember. It's important.

130
00:09:59,545 --> 00:10:02,981
我好像站在一个…
It seems I was standing in a

131
00:10:03,049 --> 00:10:06,382
是的，我站在一个大礼堂里
Yes. I was standing in a large auditorium...

132
00:10:06,452 --> 00:10:08,443
挤满了人
crowded with people.

133
00:10:08,521 --> 00:10:12,116
成千上万人紧贴在我身上，我几乎无法呼吸
Thousands pressed in against me. I could hardly breathe.

134
00:10:12,191 --> 00:10:16,628
我在为氧气而战，尖叫着要出去
I was fighting for oxygen, screaming to get out.

135
00:10:18,131 --> 00:10:20,861
不要害怕
Don't be afraid.

136
00:10:20,934 --> 00:10:24,529
我没有，但你有麻烦了
I'm not, but you are troubled.

137
00:10:24,604 --> 00:10:29,701
我似乎是我的船员中唯一留在企业号上的人
I seem to be the only one of my crew left on board the Enterprise.

138
00:10:29,776 --> 00:10:32,301
430个人
Four hundred and thirty,

139
00:10:32,378 --> 00:10:36,371
显然我是唯一留下的
and l, apparently, am the only one left.

140
00:10:37,850 --> 00:10:40,114
抱歉，我希望我能帮上忙
I'm sorry. I wish I could help.

141
00:10:40,186 --> 00:10:43,349
也许你可以，把剩下的告诉我
Maybe you can. Tell me the rest.

142
00:10:43,423 --> 00:10:48,258
你是在为氧气而战吗？尖叫着离开那里？
You were fighting for oxygen, screaming to get out of there.

143
00:10:48,328 --> 00:10:52,992
然后突然，我就在这里,在你的船上了
And then l... Suddenly I was here on this, on your ship.

144
00:10:53,066 --> 00:10:55,125
还有这么多空间
And there was all this space.

145
00:10:55,201 --> 00:10:58,967
和自由，我只想摇摆
And the freedom! I just wanted to float!

146
00:11:00,873 --> 00:11:03,637
然后你就在那里了
And then, there you were.

147
00:11:03,710 --> 00:11:06,440
你登上企业号多久了？
How long have you been aboard the Enterprise?

148
00:11:06,512 --> 00:11:09,174
我不知道，不久
I don't know. Not long.

149
00:11:10,683 --> 00:11:13,948
- 这重要吗？  - 有可能，跟我来
- Is it important? - It might be. Come with me.

150
00:11:15,922 --> 00:11:20,086
乌乎拉上尉，星际舰队回应我们的请求了吗？
Lieutenant Uhura, has Starfleet honored our request with a reply?

151
00:11:20,159 --> 00:11:22,320
还没有回应，长官
There has been no response as yet, sir.

152
00:11:22,395 --> 00:11:25,455
你有没有告诉他们舰长的生命危在旦夕？
Did you advise them the captain's life is at stake?

153
00:11:25,531 --> 00:11:29,627
是的，长官，他们坚持必须将其提交给联邦
Yes, sir. They insist the matter must be referred to the Federation.

154
00:11:29,702 --> 00:11:32,136
- 什么部门？  - 行星条约局
- What department? - The Bureau of Planetary Treaties.

155
00:11:32,205 --> 00:11:35,436
- 直接联系他们  - 我联系了，史波克先生
- Contact them directly. - I did, Mr. Spock.

156
00:11:35,508 --> 00:11:38,170
他们要求我们必须通过星际舰队的渠道
They insist that we must go through Starfleet channels.

157
00:11:43,883 --> 00:11:47,649
舰长失踪，这就是他们想出的最好的办法？
With the captain lost, that's the best they could come up with?

158
00:11:47,720 --> 00:11:51,247
外交官和官僚的职能可能不同
Diplomats and bureaucrats may function differently,

159
00:11:51,324 --> 00:11:54,555
但达到了完全相同的结果
but they achieve exactly the same results.

160
00:12:02,014 --> 00:12:05,882
我生命中少了九分钟
Nine minutes of my life has been lost.

161
00:12:05,951 --> 00:12:07,543
我不明白
I don't understand.

162
00:12:07,619 --> 00:12:09,780
从我传送到吉迪恩
Between the time I tried to beam down to Gideon...

163
00:12:09,855 --> 00:12:13,256
到发现自己在这儿，时间过了九分钟
and the time I found myself here, nine minutes have disappeared.

164
00:12:13,325 --> 00:12:18,160
- 那段时间发生了什么？  - 什么是吉迪恩？
- What happened during those minutes? - What is Gideon?

165
00:12:20,065 --> 00:12:24,297
那是你的家乡，你来的星球
That's your home, the planet that you come from.

166
00:12:24,370 --> 00:12:26,702
- 是吗？  - 嗯，一定是
- Is it? - Well, it must be.

167
